Zarak (1956 - UK)

Action / Adventure / Romance

starring . . . . Victor Mature, Michael Wilding, Anita Ekberg
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0051219/


Filmed in Burma, India, Morocco, United Kingdom

On the mountainous frontier between British India and Afghanistan, circa 1860s, Zarak Khan kisses Salma, the youngest wife of his father, Haji Khan. Outraged, his father orders Zarak to be flogged to death but spares his life at the urging of an elderly Mullah. Zarak now leaves his village and becomes a notorious outlaw, prompting the British to assign Major Ingram to capture him.
